race.comment: Excited to see the return of progressive gelding SEE YA LATER BABY (3), who looks to have more upside than these and can win first-up. He has only won a maiden but he has run well in much stronger races, including a narrow placing in the Sillabeer behind a couple of very smart horses. He's drawn low and Ben Price can give him the run of the race. MAPLEWAY (4) is race fit and was good in a similar race at Balaklava two starts back before sitting wide and having excuses last time. He is a top-three chance again. Others to consider include ROKABYE WARRIOR (8) and last-start winner BAD TO THE BONE (1).
